1.title: Whispers in the Morning
1.plot: When Chris's heart gets stabbed by a moop-infected flame sword, it's up to the rest of the Bravest Warriors to get him back safely to the ship. - in time for Beth's date with another guy.

2.title: You've Grown So Tall, You've Grown So Fast
2.plot: The Bravest Warriors are saddled with a useless Chris who's tripping crazy blocks while trying to solve a bi-dimensional baby crisis.

3.title: Mirror's Reflection
3.plot: Worm clones from another dimension overtake the hideout, forcing the real Bravest Warriors to mobilize and murder their wormy selves.

4.title: Chained to Your Side
4.plot: When her new beau stands her up for the annual 'Sadie Hawkins'-style dance, Beth flies solo for the couples' carnival games and competes against the other Bravest Warriors.

5.title: From the Inside Room
5.plot: Danny has to do the crime time for time crimes, but finds an unlikely ally in the big house.

6.title: All I Wish Is to Be Alone
6.plot: Jumpy after Puddingtown gives him an alarming tip about the other Emotion Lords, Chris, home alone, accidentally causes a violent revolt from the bathroom Elves.

7.title: This Dance Ain't for Everybody
7.plot: Beth and Plum's big 'girls night out' at a trendy virtual nightclub sours when a creepy party crasher threatens the venue and the girls' friendship.

8.title: A Few Stolen Moments
8.plot: When Beth's new boy-toy gets roped into an alien rescue mission, it's alone time with a moopy and volatile Chris that really puts him in danger.

9.title: No Need to Argue
9.plot: On a trip to her home planet, Plum's strict parents catch her and Chris partaking in forbidden nums, forcing Chris into a fight to the death with Plum's jealous ex.

10.title: We Can Leave Your Friends Behind
10.plot: Himmel begins phasing back to his own time, leaving Wallow with the hardest choice of his life: bid farewell to love, or go with him and say goodbye to the Bravest Warriors forever.

11.title: Sit Down Sip Some Bouillabaisse
11.plot: When Robochris hijacks the Space Whale for an unlikely quest, the BWs are knocked out, kidnapped, then trapped inside a living, breathing whale. After that, things get weird.

12.title: Living in a Powder Keg
12.plot: With Chris and Beth locked in the holojohn during a sassy game of 'Seven Moons in Uranus', Danny, Wallow and the pets must defend the Invisible Hideout from a Mechacat attack.

13.title: This is Not My Beautiful House
13.plot: Via a seance, Danny's mom sends him on a quest to his childhood home, where memories and a winning lottery ticket await - along with loads of sentient cockroaches.

14.title: Footsteps by the Garden Tree
14.plot: Gasp. Someone ate all the cupcakes. It's up to Detective Catbug to solve the crime and ensure the culprit gets his just deserts - which is to say, no dessert at all.

15.title: Think I'll Miss This One This Year
15.plot: Chris struggles to make it home in time to celebrate the first Thanksgiving, while the Bravest Warriors establish new holiday traditions without him.

16.title: Nothin' Stays the Same
16.plot: With the Bravest Warriors trapped in a time loop and repeatedly devoured by a Timegobbler, it's up to Beth to find an end to the cycle while experiencing infinite colorful deaths.

17.title: I.O.U. For Your Love
17.plot: When Danny is taken as the political prisoner of tiny alien bugs (on his birthday, of course), the BWs get caught up in some saucy court intrigue.

18.title: At Night When the Program's Through
18.plot: When the Invisible Hideout's food synthesizer gains sentience, the BWs name it E.D.G.A.R. and set about teaching it the mysteries of life.

19.title: All I Get is Static
19.plot: As Danny's new relationship with a super hot and totally legit girlfriend (he hasn't met in person) heats up, Beth can't figure out why Zachary Ryan is being so frosty.

20.title: I'm Smitten, I'm Bitten, I'm Hooked, I'm Cooked
20.plot: When the Bravest Warriors contract jelly pox, it's up to Catbug, Impossibear and the other pets to undertake an alien rescue mission, without anyone discovering that they aren't the real Bravest Warriors.

21.title: A (Apple) B (Banana) C (Chili)
21.plot: Wallow's hanger reaches dangerous levels, forcing the Bravest Warriors to make a quick pit stop at the Planet Mart, where they are entrapped by the lure of consumerism.

22.title: Dance into the Fire
22.plot: The war between the Emotion Lords comes to a dramatic climax in an all-out merkathon, with Beth Tezuka as the ultimate prize.

23.title: The Craft of the Father
23.plot: When Wallow discovers an abandoned alien egg, he vows to raise the baby as his own; but the high demands of parenting take a heavy toll on the teen dad.

24.title: One in a Million Girls
24.plot: As Plum and Beth hit up the mall for a robo-modelling cattle call, Chris stumbles upon some difficult truths about Zachary Ryan.

25.title: Enough to Last a Lifetime
25.plot: When Danny crash lands on a desolate planet, he finds another shipwrecked crew's holo log to guide him through his survival, escape, and consumption of alien banan'ers.

26.title: Will Things Ever Be the Same Again?
26.plot: As the Bravest Warriors go into their final throwdown with the Mecha Cats, they are uncomfortably aware of a prophecy claiming that one of them is going to get super merked.

27.title: It Shouldn't Ever Have to End this Way - Part 1
27.plot: The Courageous Battlers protect the fuzzy parts of the universe from the slimy bits, all while raising families, and lately, dealing with some - inter-office turmoil.

28.title: It Shouldn't Ever Have to End this Way - Part 2
28.plot: The Courageous Battlers were on the verge of breaking up - but now they're getting busted up by the Robolord and her army of giant Robobots.

29.title: This is Your Paradise
29.plot: Catbug doesn't care for everybody's moop over Chris's death, so he journeys into the afterlife to bring their friend back.

30.title: Too High, Too Far, Too Soon
30.plot: On a contentious Spring Break trip, the BWs find a planet where time moves super fast, and accidentally populate it with their tiny clones-who then try to destroy one another.

31.title: The Conscious Liberation of the Female State
31.plot: Beth's new role as captain of the BWs is challenged by a "Manet," a planet of only sexist dudes, that really need to simmer down and let her save them already.

32.title: Your Life is in Your Hands
32.plot: When aliens proclaim Danny to be "The One," from their ancient prophesies, Chris is suspicious and Danny is way too eager to please in his new role.

33.title: The Crowd I'm Seeing
33.plot: After breaking-up with Zachary Ryan, Beth leaves to decompress with some "me time," finding solace in a brassy all-lady gang of punky geriatrics, the "Upta Gals".

34.title: Everybody's Coming, Leave Your Body at the Door
34.plot: When the rest of the gang won't party with him, Danny invents a whole crew of RoboPartyAnimals with no 'off' buttons-and they're down to fight for their right to get down.

35.title: My Only Weakness is a List of Crime
35.plot: When the Bravest Warriors discover Catbug has been stealing "treasures" during their interplanetary adventures, Chris takes it upon himself to teach him right from wrong.

36.title: Decide What You Want From Me
36.plot: When Danny feels the Bravest Warriors would be better off without him, a strange extra-dimensional being takes him to see what life would be like if he never existed.

37.title: You're Walkin' Tough Baby But You're Walkin' Blind - Part 1
37.plot: Chris reacquaints himself with a childhood friend, while the other BWs, who remember her as a jerk, nearly destroy the hide-out with a plot to reveal her true nature.

38.title: You're Walkin' Tough Baby But You're Walkin' Blind - Part 2
38.plot: The Bravest Warriors are called to do a no-brainer task at a Wankershim parade, but find it impossible to function or keep their memories straight - what gives?.

39.title: You're Walkin' Tough Baby But You're Walkin' Blind - Part 3
39.plot: After Jenna and her gang infiltrate the Hideout, the Bravest Warriors must fight to reclaim their home and compel Chris to remember that he's on their side.

40.title: Maybe You Could Be Mine
40.plot: When he thinks Plum is in danger, Chris's Emotion Lord powers get the best of him, and he winds up stalking her super creepy-like while she runs a series of mysterious errands.

41.title: The Wire That Holds the Cork
41.plot: Danny creates a time machine that actually works. So well that it takes the BWs to a time before time, and they have to figure out how to make the Big Bang get bangin'.

42.title: If You Don't Know Electric Co.
42.plot: As Chris's wonky Emotion Lord powers are blamed for strange issues with the Space Whale, he gets cray-cray convinced that they have a secret saboteur aboard.

43.title: That Ain't Workin'
43.plot: When Danny's girlfriend breaks up with him, he handles the painful emotions like a maturing young adult - by peddling them off to blackmarket Emotion Dealer for cash.

44.title: Nice Day to Start Again
44.plot: At Plum's sister's wedding, Chris must make Plum believe in TRUE LOVE or he and the other Bravest Warriors are doomed never to experience it.

45.title: Mouth Is Alive With Juices Like Wine
45.plot: Wallow, deciding he wants to eat as ethically as possible, embarks on a faddish "ghost diet" - but the negative effects on both his physical and mental health quickly become apparent.

46.title: Bang, Bang, Bang on the Door Baby
46.plot: After a big fight about some very uncool spoilers, the Bravest Warriors retreat to separate rooms to blow off steam. But each of them causes their own kind of disaster, resulting in unexpected revelation.

47.title: I Just Can't Cope Without My Soap
47.plot: It's night shift in the E.R. as Wallow trains for his nursing credential. But when chaos erupts, he must swap bedpans for scalpels and learn the hard truths about Registered Nursing.

48.title: War Without Tears
48.plot: The Bravest Warriors discover their reality is actually a 'video game' designed to entertain Higher Beings. Lacking free will, they quickly find themselves locked in a competition to the actual death with no power to resist.

49.title: Out of Reach, Not Good Enough
49.plot: It's Plum's CURVE-VA-VERSARY, the day celebrating Plum growing legit lady bumps. But when Chris's thoughtfully planned, yet cheaply executed, party doesn't live up to her expectations, she donks herself into a series of tantrums, reliving the most lavishly decked out day of all time.

50.title: Won't You Please Take Me Home
50.plot: When the Bravest Warriors answer a distress call from a humanoid planet overrun by an evil mech race, they have no idea how their own smooshy secrets will come into play - or who they should be fighting for in the first place.

51.title: No Matter What the Future Brings - Part 1
51.plot: The Bravest Warriors journey to the See-Thru Zone to finally rescue their parents. But do the Courageous Battlers even want to be rescued?

52.title: No Matter What the Future Brings - Part 2
52.plot: With the Courageous Battlers happily trapped in the See-Thru Zone, the Bravest Warriors return to biz as usual, until they discover their parents' bliss may not be on their own volition.

1.title: Time Slime
1.plot: The Bravest Warriors must save Glendale, or be forever stuck in a time loop.

2.title: Emotion Lord
2.plot: Emotions run high on the Bravest Warriors' ship when Danny contracts Zgraxxis fever, and a crazy old man and his pork rinds may be responsible.

3.title: Butter Lettuce
3.plot: Chris, Wallow, and Danny hog the Holo-John with their fantasies.

4.title: Memory Donk
4.plot: These are the facts: the Bravest Warriors are on a bus. Their destination: somewhere. Their goal: ... something. Wait, who are the Bravest Warriors, anyway? The team must remember their identities before they crash into the NeoMars Convention Center. Things looks pretty grim for the Bravest Whoevers, but at least they have plenty of bread.

5.title: Bunless
5.plot: The fate of the planet Bunless 9 depends on the Bravest Warriors overcoming their adolescent fears of intimacy in order to prevent an apocalypse. Will love prevail through time, space, and fleshy buttocks?

6.title: Lavarinth
6.plot: The warriors must infiltrate an alien fortress to plant a bomb there without getting hopelessly lost in a maze of lava, but on their way the Emotion Lord reveals troubling secrets that may damage Chris's future.

7.title: Gas Powered Stick
7.plot: Beth's friend Plum is the hot topic in the hideout, but Impossibear's gas powered stick (which never runs out of gas) is being a nuisance. Plus, what is up with that peach pit?

8.title: Dan Before Time
8.plot: The hour has come at last! Danny has constructed a time machine so he can finally seek revenge on the low gravity hacker lads who never let him join in any of their hacker games. He reveals the truth behind his dark, disgusting past, while the team learns that revenge is meal best served cold... and kinda barfy.

9.title: Cereal Master
9.plot: In the early morning hours Chris and Danny fly from the Bravest Warriors Invisible Hideout on a mission of the utmost importance... to buy cereal for Beth. Chris must comfort a Martian chef with daddy issues and return to his best friend for their jinx-iversary.

10.title: Ultra Wankershim
10.plot: Breaking the laws of physics, Wankershim has left the Holo-John and is now taking up residence in NeoMars Park - and he's growing at an exponential rate. Meanwhile, an old friend returns to share with Chris a vision of the future, and to tell the Bravest Warriors that it's ALWAYS been Wankershim.

11.title: Catbug
11.plot: When the Bravest Warriors receive mysterious gifts from the See-Through Zone, they must use their wits to unlock the door to the greatest secret. In this season finale, there promises to be more emotion, Catbug, and delicious peanut butter squares than ever before.

12.title: Sugarbellies
12.plot: When the adorable Sugarbelly aliens ask the the Bravest Warriors for help, the young heroes split up to tackle their most challenging mission yet in this cross-planetary adventure.

13.title: Moo-Phobia
13.plot: This one-minute short shows an udderly new side of Chris Kirkman. Moove over Catbug, Chris is the star in this minisode with high steaks.

14.title: Dramabug
14.plot: Catbug puts on a soap opera show that has everyone in tears by the end.

15.title: Browser Fail
15.plot: This one-minute short features Danny who suddenly has a hair-raising dilemma. Who is the culprit behind this heinous act? Chris? Wallow? Or is it someone else?

16.title: Impossibomb
16.plot: This one-minute short features Impossibear as he hands over a present to his dear friend Wallow. But it's a BOMB. Watch this explosive new Bravest Warriors minisode to find out what happens - Nursery school.

17.title: Terrabeth Bytes
17.plot: Bring it on Wallow. This one-minute short features Beth and her Ultra Sumo Technique 509. It's a big party for the Warriors but a certain someone wasn't invited.

1.title: Aeon Worm
1.plot: Beth's "blown away" horse takes her through the inter-dimensional door to the See-Through Zone. But in this strange unnatural rift, a vile lord roams, where Beth's dad is worshipping the creature. Will Beth convince her dad to come back to the real world, or will the behemoth monster swallow them into a world of sedation? Just remember: Never doubt the worm.

2.title: Robo Chris
2.plot: In this episode, Danny gets a new #1 pal and it just so happens that he looks exactly like Chris. Does this create jealousy between the bathroom bros?

3.title: Mexican Touchdown
3.plot: Plum returns to Bravest Warriors in this hilariously action packed adventure at an alien rescue. Danny and Plum team up to help out the adorable little aliens and Catbug is wearing a grass skirt?

4.title: Hamster Priest
4.plot: Ralph Waldo Pickle Chips RETURNS. Not only that but Plum and Chris are kissing, Danny has weird eyes and Wallow is drinking his ol' beer. What the heck is up with the Warriors and what does it all mean?

5.title: Jelly Kid Forever
5.plot: Jelly Kid DIES? Who did it? Was it Wallow? Chris Kirkman the Emotion Lord? There's no way Danny did it.

6.title: The Puppetyville Horror
6.plot: Catbug assembles an away team to save the day, while the Warriors handle things on deck. Featuring friends old and new like, Impossibear, RoboChris, Halycon and Slippy Napkins who is voiced by Polly Livingston (voice of Tree Trunks from Adventure Time)

7.title: Catbug's Away Team
7.plot: Catbug assembles an away team to save the day, while the Warriors handle things on deck. Featuring friends old and new like, Impossibear, RoboChris, Halycon and Slippy Napkins who is voiced by Polly Livingston (voice of Tree Trunks from Adventure Time)

8.title: Merewif Tag
8.plot: Chris and Plum play a little Merwif Tag and little does Chris know - it makes them trade bodies. Chris with clappy pig hands and Plum with swooshy hair, and what about movie night with Beth?

9.title: Dimension Garden
9.plot: The Bravest Children come across a potential brain sucker, growing in Ralph Waldo Pickle Chip's garden and causes Wallow to become highly suspicious. You can't fool his dolls. But this doesn't bode well - Wallow needs their help.

10.title: The Parasox Pub
10.plot: Chris Kirkman is whisked away to a trans-dimensional prison/pub where he must make a difficult decision; commit a horrible murder or have a doomed future.

11.title: Season of the Worm
11.plot: In the first part of a two part finale, hamsters flee from the invisible hideout and the Bravest Warriors need to figure out what the heck is going on. Wallow receives a Falcon Mod, Danny steps it up and Beth kicks butt.

12.title: Season of the Mitch
12.plot: In the second part of the two part finale, Beth, Danny and Wallow face off against Ralph Waldo Pickle Chips and the Aeon Worm. How will they stop them from causing chaos? Watch to find out what happens.
